text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia depressa is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The dense prostrate spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.05 to 0.15 metres (0.2 to 0.5 ft). It blooms from December to January and produces yellow flowers.
